title: I Can’t Stand Britney Spears*
body:
You want to hear something funny? I can’t stand Britney Spears. Like, I won’t add her to playlists. She’s not a thought in my mind. I know some songs, but nothing will get me to like her.

And then I saw this tweet:

And out of nowhere, I was like…

Spears is a mother, who got her body back in shape, suffered emotional drama and managed to come out of it FIGHTING! She is very respectful, she kissed Maddona, can dance her ass off. I would play Britney Spears BEFORE I let one Taylor Swift track go by my ear. SHE’S A NATIONAL TREASURE!! 

Suddenly, I’m like “Britney Spears, forgive me! You’re LEAGUES better than Taylor Swift”

I may not be able to stand Britney Spears and while I don’t like the fact that they compared two women… why does it have to be Taylor Swift? 

The lesson here: when you compare Taylor Swift to anybody, you will find yourself rooting for the other person.

*actually, I can stand Britney Spears. It’s true she won’t be the first artist I’ll think about, but I will say “oh, Spears… I know of her.”

summary: I was talking to a few people last night that are going to the Taylor show Saturday and I was the oldest one being 28 and all of...
body:
I was talking to a few people last night that are going to the Taylor show Saturday and I was the oldest one being 28 and all of them between 14-19. Its so crazy to think that when I was their age at 16  I was just a bored girl watching the country countdown on the only 60 channels my grandmother got and heard Tim McGraw for the first time and now at 28 years old im seeing my first @taylorswift show.

im truly so excited even after being made fun of or called “dumb” for “wasting money” I DONT CARE! because I have and always will love Taylor Swift. So I will make my outfit, make my sign, and go with the other two girls that love her just as much as I do and have the time of our lives!!!

title: Letters to Taylor #1
body:
Dear Taylor, 

It just hit me hard right now that I’m so enternally grateful that somehow that universe lived up in a way that let me spend the most magical night with you in London. Somehow of all the tours I got to attend the reputation tour. Although I of course have loved all the other eras, and would have loved to attended the earlier tours, something about this strikes a cord with me. I don’t talk about it a lot but I’ve been on the receiving end of a lot of hate and bullying over a condition I had as a child which I had no control over. I worked really hard for years and years to get over that condition. And although it all happened when I was younger the stain on my reputation is still there. People still say this and that about me. When I first heard New Romantics during the 1989 era I got so emotional because the line “I could build a castle out of all the bricks the threw at me” was the perfect way to express what I had gone through. I had gotten so much shit thrown my way, but I had fought on and held my head high. I still remember sitting in school blasting that song in my headphones. I was so empowering to know that the person I looked up to the most knew exactly what I was feeling. Flash forward a few years and there had been quite a load of drama in the group of friends I was part of. A person I had invited back into my life turned her back on me again, even after me sitting on the phone with her for half and hour crying and begging for her to tell me what was wrong so we could fix it. I was diagnosed with an illness that put me being out of balance, physically and mentally. I am still working on recovery and trying to get somewhat back to normal. In the midst of all this you released Reputation. Not only did it brighten my days. It provided me with lyrics that I could relate to both recent and past events. It was a whole album of that empowered me in the same way New Romantics did. I realized that no matter the bad things that had happened I still had my real friends who did care about the “He said, she said.” and who stayed when it was hard or wrong or when I made mistakes. I realized that even if I have a long way to go still, I’ll eventually get back to feeling normal even with my diagnosis, and that one day all my broken bones will be mending. Getting to see you Taylor, and getting to thank you by dancing and singing my heart out, was so special. I would have loved to give you a standing ovation that lasted even longer than those three minutes at London night one. My heart aches over what you had to go trough, but I’m overjoyed that you are doing better than you ever were. I am too.

xx Emma

@taylorswift @taylornation

I wrote 11,436 words for my university degree on why Taylor Swift is a genius:

https://t.co/NMQjSiGoVv?amp=1

REPUTATION TOUR / Manc / 08.06.18

/ Wembley / 23.06.18

summary:
LONG POST ALERT! 

TAYLOR! I graduated university today! Whilst this is a big deal on its own it’s an especially big deal for me...
caption:
LONG POST ALERT!

TAYLOR! I graduated university today! Whilst this is a big deal on its own it’s an especially big deal for me as my first year of study was the worst year of my adult life. I unfortunately met someone who mentally abused me, isolated me and destroyed my confidence so I was a shell of the person I used to be.

THANKFULLY I made incredible friends who stuck by me, supported me and guided me through a time when I couldn’t even trust my own decisions. I had family who always had my best interests at heart and patiently waited for me to return back to the happy, confident person I once was. And very, very importantly I had you to guide me through those really difficult times with your music. It’s hard to explain what someone you have never met has done for your life and growth but it’s very true. Your music offered me moments of respite in my hours of despair and one day after months of dysfunction and denial that he really wasn’t all THAT bad, Dear John came on shuffle and I suddenly thought
“If it really isn’t that bad…why does this song tick every box of my relationship?”
It took me longer than I would have liked but I ended that relationship, closed that chapter of my life and moved on to not only the person I used to be, but someone better. Stronger. Wiser.

This all ends happily with my graduating from university with a degree, amazing memories and many lessons learnt. My dissertation (of which I wrote about you Taylor!) was the most challenging academic part of my university experience and was what lead me to get a 2:1, an achievement I never thought i was capable of.

So thank you SO much, Taylor. Everything you’ve ever done for me without even realising. I’m doing better than I ever was.

Love,
Becca

It took me longer than I would have liked but I ended that relationship, closed that chapter of my life and moved on to not only the person I used to be, but someone better. Stronger. Wiser.

This all ends happily with my graduating from university with a degree, amazing memories and many lessons learnt. My dissertation (of which I wrote about you Taylor!) was the most challenging academic part of my university experience and was what lead me to get a 2:1, an achievement I never thought i was capable of.

So thank you SO much, Taylor. Everything you’ve ever done for me without even realising. I’m doing better than I ever was.

Love,
Becca

“ There’s a difference between being posh and being rich.” – Kate Reardon.

  • Face Claim: Taylor Swift
  • Sexuality: Up to player

  • Faculty/Student/Staff member: Student
  • Area of study/Job:  Dance
  • Extracurricular Activities: Up to player
  • Housing on/off campus: Up to player
  • Hometown: Greenwich, CT

(+) Talented, Confident, Responsible

(-) Conceited, Condescending, Cynical

Biography:

Born in an aristocrat family, Katherine had her live solved. She was a princess through and through. With an older and a younger brother, she was the center of the Toussaint family. The was nothing she wanted that she wouldn’t get, a dangerous luxury she soon got used to.

Raised to succeed in every way she was well versed at a young age and her talent bloomed quickly in the form of Ballet. She spent hours in her private studio at their home, only accompanied by her younger brother. The only one she felt more comfortable with since they both shared the love for the arts. David was a talented pianist for a 12 years old boy.

Tragedy struck Kathy’s life when her baby brother passed away in a terrible accident at the nearest lake and without David as her companion, her heart hardened, making her conceited and sometimes cruel to others. She closed herself off and focused only on dancing.

Her reputation spoke volumes of the superficial life she was leading during her teenage years. Having a famous millionaire for a father did very little to keep her life private, and in all honesty, she didn’t care if her face was in all the magazine with thousands of rumors about her love life and her long list of disposable lovers.

It was during her twentieth birthday when life offered her an opportunity to turn into a new leaf. She had been accepted into Mousai Institute and she planned to make this the best years of her life.

                        APPLY FOR HER NOW!!!
